<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Publishing Company</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css">
    <script src="/jquery-3.7.1.min.js"></script>
</head>

<body>
    <%- include('partials/header') %>

    <section class="page-hero">
        <p class="page-eyebrow">Our Story</p>
        <h1>About Us</h1>
    </section>
    <section id="welcome">
        <div id="welcome-div">
            <p class="orange-text" id="orange-welcome-text">WELCOME TO PUBLISHING COMPANY</p>
            <h2 class="welcome-heading">Welcome to Publishing Company</h2>
            <p class="welcome-text">Far far away, behind the word mountains, far from the countries Vokalia and
                Consonantia, there live the
                blind texts. Separated they live in Bookmarksgrove right at the coast of the Semantics, a large language
                ocean. A small river named Duden flows by their place and supplies it with the necessary regelialia. It
                is a paradisematic country, in which roasted parts of sentences fly into your mouth.</p>
            <blockquote cite="https://preview.colorlib.com/theme/publishingcompany/about.html">
                Good friends, good books, and a sleepy conscience: this is the ideal life.
            </blockquote>
            <p class="welcome-text">When she reached the first hills of the Italic Mountains, she had a last view back
                on the skyline of her
                hometown Bookmarksgrove, the headline of Alphabet Village and the subline of her own road, the Line
                Lane. Pityful a rethoric question ran over her cheek, then she continued her way.</p>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section id="writers">
        <div id="writers-parent">
            <div id="writers-heading">
                <p class="orange-text">MEET OUR AUTHORS</p>
                <h2 class="welcome-heading">Authors</h2>
            </div>
            <div id="writers-cards-div">
                <div class="writers-row">
                    <div class="writers-card">
                        <div class="writer-img">
                            <img src="/images/writer-1.jpg" alt="Author's Image">
                        </div>
                        <div class="writers-info">
                            <h2>Mary Shelley</h2>
                            <p>Mary Shelley, the British author, is best known for her novel "Frankenstein". She was a prolific writer and her works continue to be popular today.</p>
                            <!-- BEGIN: View Books by Author feature -->
                            <button onclick="window.location.href='/author/' + encodeURIComponent('Mary Shelley')">View All Books</button>
                            <!-- END: View Books by Author feature -->
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="writers-card">
                        <div class="writer-img">
                            <img src="/images/writer-2.jpg" alt="Author's Image">
                        </div>
                        <div class="writers-info">
                            <h2>Anthony Hope</h2>
                            <p>Anthony Hope, the British author, is best known for his novel "The Prisoner of Zenda". He was a prolific writer and his works continue to be popular today.</p>
                            <button onclick="window.location.href='/author/' + encodeURIComponent('Anthony Hope')">View All Books</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="writers-card">
                        <div class="writer-img">
                            <img src="/images/writer-3.jpg" alt="Author's Image">
                        </div>
                        <div class="writers-info">
                            <h2>Jane Austen</h2>
                            <p>Jane Austen, the world renowned English author, completed just six works during her time and yet manages to command a legion of fans around the world.</p>
                            <button onclick="window.location.href='/author/' + encodeURIComponent('Jane Austen')">View All Books</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="writers-row">
                    <div class="writers-card">
                        <div class="writer-img">
                            <img src="/images/writer-3.jpg" alt="Author's Image">
                        </div>
                        <div class="writers-info">
                            <h2>Nemrah Ahmed</h2>
                            <p>Nemrah Ahmed is a talented writer with a passion for storytelling. Her works explore themes of identity, culture, and human relationships.</p>
                            <button onclick="window.location.href='/author/' + encodeURIComponent('Nemrah Ahmed')">View All Books</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="writers-card">
                        <div class="writer-img">
                            <img src="/images/writer-2.jpg" alt="Author's Image">
                        </div>
                        <div class="writers-info">
                            <h2>khaled hosseini</h2>
                            <p>Khaled Hosseini is a renowned Afghan-American novelist and short story writer. He is best known for his novel "The Kite Runner" and "A Thousand Splendid Suns".</p>
                            <button onclick="window.location.href='/author/' + encodeURIComponent('Khaled Hosseini')">View All Books</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="writers-card">
                        <div class="writer-img">
                            <img src="/images/writer-4.jpg" alt="Author's Image">
                        </div>
                        <div class="writers-info">
                            <h2>The Brontë Sisters</h2>
                            <p>The Brontë sisters, Charlotte, Emily, and Anne, were influential English novelists who wrote under the pseudonymsCurrer, Ellis, and Acton Bell.</p>
                            <button onclick="window.location.href='/author/' + encodeURIComponent('The Brontë Sisters')">View All Books</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </section>
